---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy notice · Blackfen Little Learners"
  description="How Blackfen Little Learners handles personal information you share through the website and enquiry form, in line with UK GDPR."
>
  <section class="py-16 md:py-20">
    <div class="container-prose">
      <p class="eyebrow mb-3">Privacy notice</p>
      <h1 class="text-balance">How we handle your information.</h1>

      <div class="mt-10 space-y-6 text-ink-700/85">
        <p>
          This notice explains what information Blackfen Little Learners
          collects through this website, why we collect it, how long we keep
          it, and what your rights are under the UK General Data Protection
          Regulation (UK GDPR) and the Data Protection Act 2018.
        </p>

        <h3>Who we are</h3>
        <p>
          Blackfen Little Learners is a home-based childminding setting in
          Blackfen, southeast London, currently in Ofsted pre-registration.
          For the purposes of UK GDPR, the data controller is
          <strong>Amy King</strong>, trading as Blackfen Little Learners.
          You can reach us at
          <a href="mailto:amy@blackfenlittlelearners.co.uk" class="underline">amy@blackfenlittlelearners.co.uk</a>
          or on 07933 177 062.
        </p>
        <p>
          Childminders in the UK are typically required to register with the
          Information Commissioner's Office (ICO) and pay an annual data
          protection fee. We're completing this registration alongside our
          Ofsted application and will add our registration number here once
          it's confirmed.
        </p>

        <h3>What we collect through this website</h3>
        <p>
          The only personal information this site asks for is what you choose
          to send through the enquiry form on the
          <a href="/contact/" class="underline">contact page</a>:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-1">
          <li>Your name</li>
          <li>Your email address</li>
          <li>Your phone number</li>
          <li>Your child's age (optional)</li>
          <li>The message you write</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          We don't run analytics, advertising trackers, or cookies of our own
          on this site. We don't ask you to create an account, and we don't
          collect anything about you in the background as you browse.
        </p>

        <h3>How we use it</h3>
        <p>
          We use the details you send through the form to reply to your
          enquiry, to talk with you about a possible place for your child,
          and — if you go on to use our service — to keep in touch about
          their care. The legal basis is your consent when you submit the
          form, and our legitimate interest in responding to people who get
          in touch about childcare.
        </p>

        <h3>Who we share it with</h3>
        <p>
          Your enquiry is delivered using
          <a href="https://resend.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="underline">Resend</a>
          (our outbound email provider) and forwarded to Amy's mailbox via
          <a href="https://www.cloudflare.com/products/email-routing/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="underline">Cloudflare Email Routing</a>
          and Google (Gmail). The site itself is hosted on
          <a href="https://pages.cloudflare.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="underline">Cloudflare Pages</a>.
          These providers process the message on our behalf so that we can
          read it. We don't sell or share your information with anyone for
          marketing, and we don't pass it to third parties for any purpose
          unrelated to your enquiry — unless we're required to by law (for
          example, in a safeguarding referral or response to a lawful
          request from Ofsted, the police, or a local authority).
        </p>

        <h3>How long we keep it</h3>
        <p>
          Enquiries that don't lead to a placement are deleted within 12
          months. If you go on to use our childcare service, we'll explain
          separately what records we keep about your child and for how long
          — most are governed by the EYFS framework and Ofsted's record-
          keeping requirements.
        </p>

        <h3>Cookies and embedded content</h3>
        <p>
          We don't set any cookies of our own. The
          <a href="/news/" class="underline">news page</a>
          embeds a single post from our Facebook page using Meta's official
          embed. When that page loads, Meta may set its own cookies in your
          browser and receive your IP address — that's controlled by Meta,
          not us. You can read more in
          <a href="https://www.facebook.com/privacy/policy" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="underline">Meta's privacy policy</a>.
          If you'd rather avoid the embed, you can read the same post
          directly on
          <a href="https://www.facebook.com/profile.php?id=61570811308988" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="underline">our Facebook page</a>
          or simply skip the news page.
        </p>

        <h3>Where your information is stored</h3>
        <p>
          Our hosting and email providers are global services and may
          process data outside the UK. Each of them publishes the safeguards
          (such as standard contractual clauses) that they rely on to keep
          transfers compliant with UK GDPR.
        </p>

        <h3>Your rights</h3>
        <p>
          You have the right to ask us what personal information we hold
          about you, to ask us to correct it if it's wrong, to ask us to
          delete it, and to object to or restrict how we use it. To exercise
          any of these rights, email
          <a href="mailto:amy@blackfenlittlelearners.co.uk" class="underline">amy@blackfenlittlelearners.co.uk</a>
          and we'll get back to you within a month.
        </p>
        <p>
          If you're unhappy with how we've handled your information, you
          can complain to the Information Commissioner's Office at
          <a href="https://ico.org.uk/make-a-complaint/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="underline">ico.org.uk/make-a-complaint</a>
          or by calling 0303 123 1113.
        </p>

        <h3>Changes to this notice</h3>
        <p>
          If we make material changes — for example, if we start using a new
          tool that handles your information — we'll update this page and
          change the date below.
        </p>

        <p class="text-sm text-ink-700/60">
          Last updated: June 2026.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
